  "title" : "Java: Path vs File",
  "body" : "<p>For new applications written in Java 7, is there any reason to use a <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/io/File.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>java.io.File</code></a> object any more or can we consider it deprecated? </p>\n\n<p>I believe a <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/nio/file/Path.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>java.nio.file.Path</code></a> can do everything a <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/io/File.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>java.io.File</code></a> can do and more.</p>\n"
